commit 7cd81f6d00eb7156f91fd435f36baa2ec93b39e0
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat Apr 11 06:43:37 2026 +0000

    fix: use --data-urlencode for user-provided values in all API URLs

    Same class of bug as the mw-fetch fix: user-provided values (page
    titles, edit summaries, continuation tokens, comments) were
    string-interpolated into URL query strings. An '&' in any value would
    split the query parameter, causing the server to receive a truncated
    value.

    Fix: use curl --data-urlencode for all parameters with user/API-provided
    values, keeping only static parameters in the URL string.

    Scripts fixed:
    - mw-page-pending-check: titles parameter
    - mw-edit: summary parameter (moved to POST body)
    - mw-file-to-url: titles parameter
    - mw-flagged-revisions-approve-page: titles, comment parameters;
      also fixed %7C double-encoding (use literal | instead)
    - mw-multi-wiki: cmtitle parameter
    - mw-all-pages: namespace and continuation token parameters

    https://claude.ai/code/session_016m6QUwiea8K33sG8uyALM5

commit 0cf0f108d54ff1b07287a26a3bb0d389e9a5613d
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat Apr 11 06:24:34 2026 +0000

    remove redundant str_replace '/' '%2F' from set_backup_filename_item

    set_backup_page_item already encodes '/' as '%2F' via
    mw-urlencode --encode-page-to-filename (Python urllib.parse.quote),
    so the str_replace was always a no-op. Now that a proper encoding tool
    exists, drop the leftover shell string replacement.

    https://claude.ai/code/session_016m6QUwiea8K33sG8uyALM5

commit 295ef9cd21f0087644d8bee4d918b9bece68a325
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat Apr 11 06:19:29 2026 +0000

    fix: use --data-urlencode for page title in mw-fetch to prevent query injection

    Page titles containing '&' were string-interpolated into the URL query,
    causing the '&' to act as a parameter separator. For example, a page
    named "Page & stuff" produced ?title=Page%20&%20stuff&action=raw, which
    the server parsed as title="Page " instead of the full title.

    Switch to curl --get --data-urlencode so each query parameter value is
    properly percent-encoded by curl itself, matching the approach already
    used (but commented out) for the POST variant on line 48-55.

    https://claude.ai/code/session_016m6QUwiea8K33sG8uyALM5

commit 89651ba4e35a6a479cc67183758d4bf049d23242
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat Apr 11 06:09:01 2026 +0000

    fix: add assert_path_within_dir guard in mw-wiki-push-backup

    The file_path constructed from git diff --name-only output was not
    validated against directory traversal. A malicious .mw filename in
    the git repo (e.g. ../../../etc/shadow.mw) could escape backup_dir.

    https://claude.ai/code/session_01TxoWHU6zPbn2d5CRpZgU4g

