commit 92c01bb466f41c6b6cb4546fbf1879533dffb72d
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat Apr 11 05:12:47 2026 +0000

    fix: wrong page name in approve-all and missing password write in login

    mw-flagged-revisions-approve-all: passed filesystem-encoded
    $backup_page_item (e.g. Dev%2Fcompiler_hardening) to the MediaWiki API
    instead of the raw $item_from_all_pages. This broke approval for any
    page whose title contains /, &, #, ?, or %.

    mw-login: the comment said "Write password to a temp file" but the
    actual write was missing. mktemp created an empty file, so
    --data-urlencode "lgpassword@${pass_file}" always sent an empty
    password.

