    fix: use $new_file instead of hardcoded path in mw-patch-modify-wiki-page

    Line 49 hardcoded filename="$TMPFOLDER/fetched-wiki-page" instead of
    using $new_file (the actual output path from arg 3). When called from
    mw-process-all-pages, TMPFOLDER is overridden to a per-page subdirectory,
    so the hardcoded path pointed to a nonexistent file while the fetched
    content was at $new_file. This caused replace_all_except_first and
    mw-edit to operate on nothing.

