commit b93878bcef7bdc7396bd30ad49ce5840e0b4ccf0
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat Apr 11 04:30:37 2026 +0000

    fix: don't filesystem-encode page names for API calls in approve-all

    mw-flagged-revisions-approve-all was passing page names through
    set_backup_page_item() (filesystem encoding) before handing them to
    mw-flagged-revisions-approve-page, which uses them as raw page titles
    in MediaWiki API query strings.

    For pages with special characters (& % # ? etc.), the filesystem
    percent-encoding caused wrong page titles in the API requests.
    For example, 'Page & stuff' was encoded to 'Page_%26_stuff' then
    used in &titles=Page_%26_stuff where the server decodes %26 to &,
    splitting the query parameter.

    Pass the raw page name directly since no filesystem path is involved.

    https://claude.ai/code/session_019HZFzBFAgxnsS5ZBaz9irT

commit 8737983d4a009e5cac732142e034d18f63790f87
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri Apr 10 19:26:56 2026 +0000

    fix incomplete filename decoding in mw-wiki-push-backup

    The push script only decoded %2F back to /, silently leaving all other
    percent-encoded characters (%26, %25, %23, %3F, etc.) in the page title.
    Pages containing &, %, #, ? or other encoded characters would be pushed
    to the wrong wiki page.

    Replace the manual partial decode with decode_backup_filename_item(),
    which already exists in common and performs full urllib.parse.unquote.

    https://claude.ai/code/session_019HZFzBFAgxnsS5ZBaz9irT

