commit 4c41a7b59af616227d48ab6b83e17cbde77045c6
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri Apr 10 18:23:38 2026 +0000

    add validate_safe_filename to set_backup_filename_item

    Defense-in-depth: validate the final filename in set_backup_filename_item
    too, not just in set_backup_page_item. Both functions now validate their
    output.

    NOTE: validate_safe_filename in helper-scripts/strings.bsh does not
    currently allow '%' in its character whitelist. This must be fixed in
    the helper-scripts package by adding '%' to the allowed regex:
      re='^[][:alnum:]_.:@+=,(){}%\[ -]+$'
    Without that fix, percent-encoded filenames like 'Dev%2Fcompiler_hardening'
    will fail validation with "Invalid character!".

    https://claude.ai/code/session_01W8Ge7qTXTEQjAYHqYaZ9bg

