commit 3e30c4383e8de6ea746ddc7398bb6f51648c5570
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri Apr 10 17:40:06 2026 +0000

    clarify colon safety and space/underscore round-trip in docstrings

    - Document why ':' is intentionally in _FILENAME_SAFE: Linux-only tool,
      colon is valid on Linux filesystems, and MediaWiki namespaces
      (Template:, Category:, File:) use it extensively.
    - Clarify that encode/decode round-trip is in the MediaWiki sense:
      spaces and underscores are identical in MediaWiki page titles, so
      'Page name' -> 'Page_name' -> 'Page_name' is a correct round-trip.
    - Note in decode docstring that underscores are left as-is intentionally.

