commit a10e110069cc97b83ed96a97a24d0d01b51b074a
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri Apr 10 17:19:46 2026 +0000

    refactor: use Python urllib.parse for filename encoding/decoding

    Replace the hand-rolled bash str_replace chain in set_backup_page_item
    and decode_backup_page_item with Python's urllib.parse.quote/unquote
    (standard RFC 3986 percent-encoding).

    mw-urlencode gains two new modes:
      --encode-page-to-filename  encode page name to safe filename
      --decode-filename-to-page  decode filename back to page name

    The legacy mode (mw-urlencode <URL>) is unchanged.

    Benefits:
    - Standard percent-encoding instead of ad-hoc replacements
    - Handles all unsafe characters (not just /, &, space, %)
    - Properly handles unicode, double-encoding edge cases
    - Single source of truth in Python, no bash reimplementation
    - '&' now uses standard '%26' instead of '#ampersand#'

    https://claude.ai/code/session_01W8Ge7qTXTEQjAYHqYaZ9bg

commit a2a3b4617d4cfd0c88688c9aa63918ae67ad88d4
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
