    harden mw-wiki-fetch-backup and add decode safety warning

    - mw-wiki-fetch-backup: pipe raw page name through set_backup_page_item
      before set_backup_filename_item, so '%' and '&' are also encoded for
      the temp file path (previously only '/' was encoded)
    - Add warning comment on decode_backup_page_item: decoded output
      restores '/' and must only be used as API parameters, never for
      file path construction

    https://claude.ai/code/session_01W8Ge7qTXTEQjAYHqYaZ9bg

commit a3083e7e89f77e2bddfeb61164d3c229f747cf39
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri Apr 10 14:58:23 2026 +0000

    add defense-in-depth against directory traversal in file path construction

    Wiki page names from the API are used to construct local file paths.
    Although the encoding now replaces '/' with '%2F' and MediaWiki itself
    forbids '..' in page titles, add an explicit path containment check
    as defense-in-depth.

    - Add assert_path_within_dir() to common: uses realpath to verify
      the resolved target path is inside the expected base directory.
      Catches traversal via '..', symlinks, or any encoding bypass.
    - Add assertions in mw-process-all-pages, mw-wiki-fetch-backup,
      mw-copy-wiki-pages, and mw-copy-wiki-file at all points where
      wiki-derived names are joined into file paths.

    https://claude.ai/code/session_01W8Ge7qTXTEQjAYHqYaZ9bg

commit 69f2a680fbd3042c46618dc67d249d829fb5652e
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri Apr 10 13:57:37 2026 +0000

    fix lossy filename encoding for subpages with '/' in page names

    set_backup_page_item replaced both ' ' and '/' with '_', making
    backup/restore round-trip impossible for subpages like
    'Dev/compiler_hardening' (became 'Dev_compiler_hardening.mw',
    indistinguishable from a page named 'Dev compiler_hardening').

    - Change '/' encoding from '_' to '%2F' (percent-encoding)
    - Add '%' -> '%25' escaping first to handle literal '%' in page names
    - Add decode_backup_page_item and decode_backup_filename_item functions
      for reversing the encoding during restore

